result.formatted_address: 200 Hollywood Rd, Sheung Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: For Kee Restaurant

reviews.text: This is one of those back alley local spots that I LOVE to find when traveling. They serve simple local dishes cooked just the way you would expect them to be served at home in a HK household. DO NOT MISS the cold coffee tea on a hot day (yes you heard right its coffee mixed with tea and its AWESOME). The staff are really and accommodating and even helped us with the menu as we don't speak mandarin. Only a short walk from the subway so if you're in the area it is worth seeking out.

Whoa. Definitely have to go here. I didn't think a pork chop sounded very appetizing, so I waited until the end of our trip to go here. Don't wait. Get the pork chop rice with vegetable and the tomato pork chop rice. Eat it with the spicy sauce too. Already miss it.

Got the pork chop rice plus drink lunch set for $56. Tasty but not special. Setting is typical grassroot neighborhood type so expect to share table in an already cramped space, hence some discomfort. But given the cost quality of food, still good value for money.
Pork chop rice with fried eggs is very good. I like it!!

Pork chop rice with fried eggs is good but coffee is a bit too sour for my taste.
Worth trying.

reviews.text: 雨宿りがわりに ミルクティーとハムサンドを軽くいただきました。何気ないものだけどトーストごカリッとして美味しかったトースト思います。中は庶民的で懐かしい感じ 相席で地元の人たちと近い感じがいいですね。お店のお兄さんさんは口数少ないけど 言葉が分からない私に気遣ってくれていたのがわかりました。

이런류의 로컬식당 가본곳 중 가장 깨끗했습니다. 음식도 맛있었는데 특히 머쉬룸 볶음밥이 정말 맛있었어요. 메뉴중에선 비싼편이지만 양이 많아서 둘이 먹어도 적당히 배부를 양입니다. 후기중에 별로라는 얘기가 있던 밀크티도 홍콩에서 먹어본 것 중 제일 맛있게 먹었네요. 역시 취향차이겠죠? 멀리서 일부러 찾아가야할 정도는 아니지만 근처에 숙소 있으신 분들이나 근방에 오실일 있는 분들이라면 완전 추천!!
由細食到大, 以前是大排檔, 这里豬扒好味到不得了，可惜近年太多客人, 不容易找到坐子, 且價錢不便宜

見到門口大大隻字寫豬扒. 
一般般. 肉質係無用梳打乸過, 個汁係透明. 有啲怪. 奶茶無咩茶味. 唔澀. 一般般
